{
  "answer": "**The specific moment occurs after Andrew (Andreas) is first captured by the Mermedonians, bound, dragged through the streets, and scourged all day until evening.**[^1]\n\nThe text states:  \n> The people then led their loathed enemy  \n> to the prison.[^1]\n\nThis marks his initial imprisonment following capture (lines around 1405–1410 in standard editions). He is later led out for further torments and returned to the prison multiple times (e.g., after the second and third days of scourging), but this is the first instance.\n\n[^1]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-5d78fc).",
